An overview of the main trends of the development of Estonian theatre and drama from the initial stage up to the present is given: the development of the theatre institutsion, the role of the theatre in the Estonian society and culture (including the relationship with literature), the most essential artistic trends, the work of the outstanding directors. The lectures are illustrated with the video recordings.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. has an general overview of the periods of Estonian theatre history, understands the chronology
2. knows the most important theatre directors and associates them to the main historic periods
3. analysis the classics of Estonian dramaturgy and associates them to the main historic periods
4. is able to place theatrical processes to the context of  general history and sees their relationsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student A student knows main features of the history of Estonian theatre and drama: changes of theatrical system, main artistic trends (Realism, Modernism, Postmodernism, etc), functions of the theatre. A student  knows how to analyse the work of outstanding stage directors and playwrights and how to relate it with historical context.
